{"id":"pottage","term":"Pottage","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Heb. nazid, “boiled”, a dish of boiled food, as of lentils (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 25:29\">Gen. 25:29</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 4:38\">2 Kings 4:38</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Genesis 25:29","2 Kings 4:38"]}